  abstract     = {Virulent phages can expose their bacterial hosts to
                  devastating epidemics, in principle leading to complete
                  elimination of their hosts. Although experiments indeed
                  confirm a large reduction of susceptible bacteria, there are
                  no reports of complete extinctions. We here address this
                  phenomenon from the perspective of spatial organization of
                  bacteria and how this can influence the final survival of
                  them. By modelling the transient dynamics of bacteria and
