                  bacteriophage infections. Previous authors have proposed
                  systems of ordinary differential delay equations with delay
                  dependent coefficients. In this paper we continue these
                  studies in two respects. First, we show that the dynamics is
                  sensitive to the phage mortality function, and in particular
                  to the parameter we use to measure the density dependent phage
                  mortality rate. Second, we incorporate spatial effects by
                  deriving, in one spatial dimension, a delay reaction-diffusion
                  model in which the delay term is rigorously derived by solving
